<p>
  If you have started looking for a private app for couples, two names come up everywhere: <strong>Paired</strong> and <strong>OurCouple</strong>. Both promise to bring you closer to your partner, but they take very different approaches. I have used both with my partner over the past few months. Here is the honest comparison.
</p>

<h2>The Short Version</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Paired</strong> is a daily-questions app. The whole product revolves around answering one prompt a day with your partner and reading expert relationship articles.</li>
  <li><strong>OurCouple</strong> is an all-in-one shared space. Daily messages and photos, shared memories, love notes, an event calendar, and even a virtual pet you take care of together — all in one private app.</li>
</ul>

<p>
  If you only want a daily conversation prompt, Paired works fine. If you want a single private place to actually live your relationship together — messages, memories, plans, and milestones — OurCouple is the better fit.
</p>

