<h2>Pricing</h2>

<p>
  This is where the difference gets real. Paired charges <em>per user</em>. If you and your partner both want premium, you pay twice. OurCouple uses a shared-subscription model — one premium plan unlocks everything for both of you. Over a year, that's a meaningful difference.
</p>

<h2>Privacy</h2>

<p>
  OurCouple encrypts your shared content end-to-end. Paired stores conversation answers on their servers in a way that staff could read them if needed. If your relationship data matters to you (it should), this is a real distinction. We covered it in detail in <a href="/blog/relationship-data-encryption">why your relationship data deserves encryption</a>.
</p>

<h2>Who Each App Is For</h2>

<h3>Choose Paired if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You only want a daily conversation prompt and expert articles</li>
  <li>You don't mind paying separately from your partner</li>
  <li>You don't need a shared journal or photo memories</li>
</ul>

<h3>Choose OurCouple if…</h3>
<ul>
  <li>You want one private place that does everything</li>
  <li>You care about end-to-end encryption</li>
  <li>You want one subscription that covers both partners</li>
  <li>You like daily rituals (a message, a photo, a love note) more than long quizzes</li>
</ul>

<h2>Other Alternatives Worth Knowing</h2>

<p>
  If neither sounds right, we ranked the <a href="/blog/best-couples-journal-apps">best couples journal apps in 2026</a> with deeper reviews of Lasting, Between, Couple, and others.
</p>

<h2>The Bottom Line</h2>

<p>
  Paired is a focused tool for couples who want daily prompts and relationship reading. OurCouple is a full private space for couples who want their daily life — messages, photos, memories, notes, plans — to live in one private app, encrypted, with a single subscription for both. Pick the one that matches how you actually want to use it.
</p>

